[thinking] I need to address the DebuggerService singleton problem. If tests run in the same JVM, a class can set the port and initialize the service. There are existing tests that use system properties, but after calling DebuggerService.shutdown, the service instance stays active while the server stops. This could cause issues with getBreakpoints calls to the stopped service. It’s important to ensure each test class is isolated to avoid failures due to order dependencies. Maybe using separate forks for each test class could help?
