s initialization and method coverage occur during class initialization. It seems like under Native Image, class initialization might happen at build time instead of at runtime. If that’s the case, dynamic access wouldn't happen at runtime. JaCoCo JVM coverage seems acceptable, but I wonder if dynamic access relies on monitoring by a compile-time agent during static analysis. I’m considering how the tests execute, and whether they might trigger initialization or if I can cover this with JVM tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Class.forName and native builds**\\n\\nI’m wondering what happens if Class.forName is unsupported. It seems that an existing direct Class.forName catches errors during the Native runtime, but a new stub might fail at the native build if class initialization runs with missing reflection. It’s unclear. Native image builds initialize many app classes at runtime by default unless they are considered safe. I think reflection in the class initialization could fail with an ExceptionInInitializerError, but catching errors might still be possible.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fLoGe37vNbEqP3dmyNH4xdRo|fc_0d9a5266f308cffb0169f497cbb62c81939542e300d98f33f7", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggedEnvironmentImplStubTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage fm;\n\nimport java.io.ObjectOutput;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.rmi.Remote;\nimport java.rmi.RemoteException;\nimport java.rmi.server.Operation;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteCall;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;\n\nimport freemarker.debug.DebuggedEnvironment;\nimport freemarker.debug.impl.RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub;\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggedEnvironmentImplStubTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void initializesGeneratedRmiDebuggedEnvironmentStub() {\n        DebuggedEnvironment environment = new RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub(new RecordingRemoteRef());\n\n        Assertions.assertThat(environment)\n                .isInstanceOf(RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub.class);\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingRemoteRef implements RemoteRef {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        @Override\n        public Object invoke(Remote remote, Method method, Object[] parameters, long operation)\n                throws RemoteException {\n            throw new RemoteException(\"No remote endpoint is configured for this test stub\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public RemoteCall newCall(RemoteObject object, Operation[] operations, int operation, long hash)\n                throws RemoteException {\n            throw new RemoteException(\"No remote endpoint is configured for this test stub\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void invoke(RemoteCall call) throws RemoteException {\n            throw new RemoteException(\"No remote endpoint is configured for this test stub\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void done(RemoteCall call) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String getRefClass(ObjectOutput output) {\n            return \"recording\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int remoteHashCode() {\n            return System.identityHashCode(this);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public boolean remoteEquals(RemoteRef remoteRef) {\n            return this == remoteRef;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public String remoteToString() {\n            return \"RecordingRemoteRef\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/jav