st class rules**\\n\\nI’m focusing on the rules about using `$` in test class or file names, and I’m wondering if inner classes are okay since existing tests use them. It seems manageable to write a class file patcher. I need to avoid importing RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub to prevent original initialization. Direct imports should be removed, and I’m thinking about using Assertions on class names or class loaders. If needed, I could try to instantiate or load patched classes with reflection, but I must be cautious about direct reflection in tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Editing class loading pattern**\\n\\nIt seems like they’re referring specifically to the dynamic class loading pattern, which is important to keep in mind. I realize that I need to edit the file significantly, so using a method to write the whole file makes sense. It’s all about ensuring I get the details right in the implementation, so let’s proceed carefully and make those necessary changes accordingly! I want to make sure everything lines up just as needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xKUFjqGoZj75VugFXTcsdLFi|fc_0d9a5266f308cffb0169f499f958048193a4fb7b85d8c802b8", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggedEnvironmentImplStubTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage fm;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggedEnvironmentImplStubTest {\n    private static final String STUB_CLASS_NAME = \"freemarker.debug.impl.RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub\";\n    private static final String STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE = \"freemarker/debug/impl/RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub.class\";\n    private static final String STUB_SOURCE_FILE = \"RmiDebuggedEnvironmentImpl_Stub.java\";\n\n    @Test\n    void initializesGeneratedRmiDebuggedEnvironmentStubWithFreshClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            ClassLoader parentClassLoader = FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggedEnvironmentImplStubTest.class.getClassLoader();\n            ClassLoader stubClassLoader = new StubOnlyClassLoader(parentClassLoader);\n\n            Class<?> stubClass = Class.forName(STUB_CLASS_NAME, true, stubClassLoader);\n\n            Assertions.assertThat(stubClass.getName()).isEqualTo(STUB_CLASS_NAME);\n            Assertions.assertThat(stubClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(stubClassLoader);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.findClass(name);\n            }\n\n            byte[] classBytes = readStubClassBytes();\n            byte[] debuggableClassBytes = ClassFileDebugInfoPatcher.addDebugInfo(classBytes);\n            return defineClass(name, debuggableClassBytes, 0, debuggableClassBytes.length);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] readStubClassBytes() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            try (InputStream inputStream = getParent().getResourceAsStream(STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE)) {\n                if (inputStream == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME);\n                }\n                return inputStream.readAllBytes();\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME, e);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ClassFileDebugInfoPatcher {\n        private static final int CLASS_INITIALIZER_LINE = 1;\n        private static final int CLASS_RESOLUTION_HELPER_LINE = 2;\n\n        private ClassFileDebugInfoPatcher() {\n        }\n\n        static byte[] addDebugInfo(byte[] classBytes) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            try {\n                ClassReader reader = new ClassReader(classBytes);\n                ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream(classBytes.length + 128);\n                ClassWriter writer = new ClassWriter(output);\n\n                writer.writeInt(reader.readInt());\n                writer.writeShort(reader.readUnsignedShort());\n                writer.writeShort(reader.readUnsignedShort());\n\n                int constantPoolCount = reader.readUnsignedShort();\n                String[] constantPoolUtf8 = new String[constantPoolCount + 3];\n                writer.writeShort(constantPoolCount + 3);\n                copyConstantPool(reader, writer, constantPoolCount, constantPoolUtf8);\n                int sourceFileAttributeNameIndex = constantPoolCount;\n                int lineNumberTableAttributeNameIndex = constantPoolCount + 1;\n                int sourceFileNameIndex = constantPoolCount + 2;\n                writer.writeUtf8Constant(\"SourceFile\");\n                writer.writeUtf8Constant(\"LineNumberTable\");\n                writer.writeUtf8Constant(STUB_SOURCE_FILE);\n\n                writer.writeBytes(reader.readBytes(6));\n                int interfacesCount = reader.readUnsignedShort();\n                writer.writeShort(interfacesCount);\n                writer.writeBytes(reader.readBytes(interfacesCount * 2));\n\n                int fieldsCount = reader.readUnsignedShort();\n                writer.writeShort(fieldsCount);\n                copyMembers(reader, writer, fieldsCount);\n\n                int methodsCount = reader.readUnsignedShort();\n                writer.writeShort(methodsCount);\n                for (int methodIndex = 0; methodIndex < methodsCount; methodIndex++) {\n                    copyMethod(reader, writer, constantPoolUtf8, lineNumberTableAttributeNameIndex);\n                }\n\n                int classAttributesCount = reader.readUnsignedShort();\n                writer.writeShort(classAttributesCount + 1);\n                copyAttributes(reader, writer, classAttributesCount);\n                writer.writeShort(sourceFileAttributeNameIndex);\n                writer.writeInt(2);\n                writer.writeShort(sourceFileNameIndex);\n\n                Assertions.assertThat(reader.isAtEnd()).isTrue();\n                return output.toByteArray();\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME, e);\n            }\n        }\n\n        private static void copyConstantPool(\n                ClassReader reader,\n                ClassWriter writer,\n                int constantPoolCount,\n                String[] constantPoolUtf8\n        ) throws IOException {\n            for (int index = 1; index < constantPoolCount; index++) {\n                int tag = reader.readUnsignedByte();\n                writer.writeByte(tag);\n                switch 